name: Zucchilattas
author: Barbie
summary: This is a great way to use some of the fresh garden vegetables abundant at this time of year. Zucchini, mushrooms, onion, and tomatoes are cooked until tender, wrapped in warm tortillas, topped with cheese and baked until bubbly.
ingredients: 1 ½ pounds Monterey Jack cheese, shredded
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Lightly grease a 9x13 inch baking dish
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat
Mix together the zucchini, mushrooms, onion, tomatoes, salt and pepper, and add to the skillet
Cook and stir until the vegetables are soft
Warm the tortillas 2 to 3 minutes, until soft, in the preheated oven
Fill the warmed tortillas with zucchini mixture and Monterey Jack cheese, reserving some of both for toppings
Roll the filled tortillas and place them seam side down in the baking dish
Cover with the remaining zucchini mixture
Bake in the preheated oven 15 minutes, or until the cheese is bubbly
